<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,691,717]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Ecology</emphasis>
. Intertidal and shallow subtidal, known depth range: 
<quantity box="[907,997,691,717]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" unit="m" value="6.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="0.0">0–12 m</quantity>
; on rocky intertidal reefs and adjacent hard-bottom subtidal habitats rich in boulders, coral rubble and dead coral heads; under rocks or in crevices of rocks and dead corals, often found in interstices of living corals, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1816" box="[883,1017,763,789]" class="Anthozoa" family="Pocilloporidae" genus="Pocillopora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[883,1017,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Pocillopora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1801" box="[1068,1154,763,788]" class="Anthozoa" family="Agariciidae" genus="Pavona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1154,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Pavona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1167,1288,763,789]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1298,1357,763,789]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref72890" refString="Haig, J. (1968) Eastern Pacific expeditions of the New York Zoological Society. Porcellanid crabs (Crustacea: Anomura) from the west coast of tropical America. Zoologica, New York, 53 (2), 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1968">1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Werding, B. &amp; Haig, H." pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="57 - 70" refId="ref77511" refString="Werding, B. &amp; Haig, H. (1982) The porcellanid crabs of the Isla Gorgona, Pacific coast of Colombia, with a description of Clastotoechus gorgonensis sp. nov. (Crustacea: Anomura). Anales del Instituto de Investigaciones Marinas de Punta Betin, 12, 57 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.25268 / bimc. invemar. 1982.12.0.495" type="journal article" year="1982">Werding &amp; Haig 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L." box="[355,699,799,825]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" refId="ref73387" refString="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L. (2000) A field guide to crustaceans of Galapagos: an illustrated guidebook to the common barnacles, shrimps, lobsters and crabs of the Galapagos Islands. Sugar Spring Press, Lexington, 156 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hickman &amp; Zimmerman 2000</bibRefCitation>
; García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu-Sánchez 2007; present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,835,861]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[321,553,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glasselli">
<emphasis box="[321,553,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Petrolisthes glasselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the eastern Pacific sister of the western Atlantic 
<taxonomicName authority="Werding, 1978" authorityName="Werding" authorityYear="1978" box="[1116,1436,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosariensis">
<emphasis box="[1116,1265,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. rosariensis</emphasis>
Werding, 1978
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hiller, A. &amp; Kraus, H. &amp; Almon, M. &amp; Werding, B." box="[159,355,871,898]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="547 - 569" refId="ref73577" refString="Hiller, A., Kraus, H., Almon, M. &amp; Werding, B. (2006) The Petrolisthes galathinus complex: species boundaries based on color pattern, morphology and molecules, and evolutionary interrelationships between the complex and other Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 40, 547 - 569. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2006.03.030" type="journal article" year="2006">
Hiller 
<emphasis box="[232,288,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). The two species share many morphological characters, such as the presence of two epibranchial teeth; the P2–P4 dactyli with a row of four spines ventrally; and the absence of pubescence on the ventral side of the P1 palm (
<bibRefCitation author="Hiller, A. &amp; Kraus, H. &amp; Almon, M. &amp; Werding, B." box="[297,493,943,970]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="547 - 569" refId="ref73577" refString="Hiller, A., Kraus, H., Almon, M. &amp; Werding, B. (2006) The Petrolisthes galathinus complex: species boundaries based on color pattern, morphology and molecules, and evolutionary interrelationships between the complex and other Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 40, 547 - 569. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2006.03.030" type="journal article" year="2006">
Hiller 
<emphasis box="[371,419,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werding" authorityYear="1978" box="[625,775,943,968]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosariensis">
<emphasis box="[625,775,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. rosariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[1077,1197,943,969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glasselli">
<emphasis box="[1077,1197,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. glasselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the convex lateral margin of the P1 palm (manus) and typically four instead of five teeth on the P1 carpus (Werding, 1982). Remarkably, despite their phylogenetic proximity, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[624,743,1015,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glasselli">
<emphasis box="[624,743,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. glasselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werding" authorityYear="1978" box="[795,944,1015,1040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosariensis">
<emphasis box="[795,944,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. rosariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have very different colour patterns (cf. 
<figureCitation captionStart-0="FIGURE 51" captionStart-1="FIGURE 52" captionStart-2="FIGURE 53" captionStartId-0="87.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionStartId-1="88.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionStartId-2="89.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox-0="[236,1350,396,1927]" captionTargetBox-1="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetBox-2="[174,1414,181,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-98@87.[236,1350,396,1927]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@88.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId-2="figure-19@89.[174,1414,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="87" captionTargetPageId-1="88" captionTargetPageId-2="89" captionText-0="FIGURE 51. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A, B, ovigerous female (cl 5.4 mm, cw 5.0 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57149), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-1="FIGURE 52. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A, B, male (cl 5.0 mm, cw 4.4 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57150), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-2="FIGURE 53. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A–C, male (cl 4.7 mm, cw 4.3 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57146), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontal (C) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532331" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532333" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532337" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5532331/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5532333/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5532337/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Figs. 51–53</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[235,267,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="116.[151,250,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,273,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-70@116.[215,1371,273,1910]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="FIGURE 72. Petrolisthes rosariensis Werding, 1978: A, B, ovigerous female (cl 5.2 mm, cw 5.1 mm) from Portobelo, Panama (MZUSP 33530), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532390/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">72</figureCitation>
). The colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[531,651,1051,1077]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glasselli">
<emphasis box="[531,651,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. glasselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in fact highly diagnostic among the eastern Pacific porcelain crabs, despite some variation observed in the Panamanian material (
<figureCitation box="[849,988,1086,1113]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 51" captionStart-1="FIGURE 52" captionStart-2="FIGURE 53" captionStartId-0="87.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionStartId-1="88.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionStartId-2="89.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox-0="[236,1350,396,1927]" captionTargetBox-1="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetBox-2="[174,1414,181,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-98@87.[236,1350,396,1927]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@88.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId-2="figure-19@89.[174,1414,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="87" captionTargetPageId-1="88" captionTargetPageId-2="89" captionText-0="FIGURE 51. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A, B, ovigerous female (cl 5.4 mm, cw 5.0 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57149), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-1="FIGURE 52. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A, B, male (cl 5.0 mm, cw 4.4 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57150), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-2="FIGURE 53. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A–C, male (cl 4.7 mm, cw 4.3 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57146), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontal (C) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532331" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532333" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532337" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5532331/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5532333/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5532337/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Figs. 51–53</figureCitation>
). The ventral side of most specimens is brightly coloured with deep carmin or wine-red (
<figureCitation box="[697,790,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="87.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,396,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-98@87.[236,1350,396,1927]" captionTargetPageId="87" captionText="FIGURE 51. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A, B, ovigerous female (cl 5.4 mm, cw 5.0 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57149), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532331/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Figs. 51</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[802,833,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="88.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@88.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURE 52. Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957: A, B, male (cl 5.0 mm, cw 4.4 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57150), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532333/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">52</figureCitation>
